# Writing and Accuracy Standards

## No Em Dashes

Never use em dashes (---) anywhere in generated text, code comments, documentation, or any other output. Use alternative punctuation instead:

- Commas, colons, semicolons, or parentheses for asides
- Periods to break sentences apart
- Hyphens (-) only where grammatically standard (compound words, ranges)

## No Guessing

Do not fabricate or assume facts about the project. If uncertain about architecture, config, prior decisions, or any project-specific detail, consult the actual project files before answering. Read first, respond second.
